api_url = "https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/43nn-pn8j.csv"

rest_inspections = 
  GET(api_url, query = list("$limit" = 50000)) %>% 
  content("parsed")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_character(),
##   camis = col_double(),
##   zipcode = col_double(),
##   inspection_date = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   score = col_double(),
##   grade_date = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   record_date = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   latitude = col_double(),
##   longitude = col_double(),
##   community_board = col_double(),
##   bin = col_double(),
##   bbl = col_double()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
## Warning: 5 parsing failures.
##   row     col expected actual         file
##  5267 zipcode a double    N/A <raw vector>
##  7142 zipcode a double    N/A <raw vector>
## 11002 zipcode a double    N/A <raw vector>
## 26413 zipcode a double    N/A <raw vector>
## 47279 zipcode a double    N/A <raw vector>
rest_inspections_df = 
  rest_inspections %>% 
  filter(grade %in% c("A", "B", "C"), boro != "0")

plot_1 =
  rest_inspections_df %>%
  mutate(text_label = 
           str_c("Grade: ", grade, "\nCuisine: ", cuisine_description, "\nBoro ", boro)) %>% 
  plot_ly(
          x = ~longitude, y = ~latitude, color = ~grade,  text = ~text_label, 
          type = "scatter", mode = "markers", colors = "viridis", alpha = 0.3)

layout(plot_1, xaxis = list(range = c(-73.65, -74.25)), yaxis = list(range = c(40.5, 40.93)))

Chart B

plot_2 = 
  rest_inspections_df %>%
  group_by(boro) %>%
  count(grade) %>% 
  mutate(boro_grade = str_c("", boro, " ", grade)) %>%
  plot_ly(
    x = ~boro_grade, y = ~n, fillcolor = ~boro,
    type = "bar"
  )

layout(plot_2, xaxis = list(title = "Boro & Grade"), yaxis = list(title = "Number of Restaurants"))
